<title>SINGAPORE: Singapore April retail sales fall 0.9 pct on yr.</title>
<headline>Singapore April retail sales fall 0.9 pct on yr.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-05-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Singapore's retail sales index (base 1991) fell 0.9 percent in April compared to a year ago, the Statistics Department said on Thursday.  </p>
<p>The index was down 6.4 percent compared with March.</p>
<p>Excluding motor vehicles, the index registered a month-on-month drop of 7.6 percent in April.</p>
<p>Total April retail sales were estimated at Singapore $1.98 billion.</p>
<p>The report said that year-on-year, in constant prices, the retail index rose by 0.3 percent.  </p>
<p>					 Month-on-month     Yr-on-yr</p>
<p>    Total index			   -6.4		-0.9</p>
<p>    X-vehicle sales		     -7.6		 4.6</p>
<p>    Textiles/apparels		  -12.3		 7.8</p>
<p>    Furniture/household equipment  -10.0		13.6</p>
<p>    Motor vehicles			-1.6	     -16.5</p>
<p>    Petrol stations			4.4		-3.1</p>
<p>    Department stores/supermarkets  -5.4		 0.5</p>
<p>    General provisions		  -2.3		 6.6</p>
<p>    Other retail			  -8.9		 2.3</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703199)</p>
